    "created_at": "2012-11-13T12:56:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-11-13T12:56:32Z",
    "body": "I don't think there's a lot of memory allocation going on SublimeClang side so either there's a leak or that's just how much memory libclang uses. You can manually clear the cache via goto anything (search \"clear cache\") and change the [index_parse_options](https://github.com/quarnster/SublimeClang/blob/7c30b9ed2e932d2b65588bd9e4168a213dd6de12/SublimeClang.sublime-settings#L81) setting to something different as a first attack vector.\r\n\r\nBeyond that you'd have to investigate what the [libclang resource usage](http://clang.llvm.org/doxygen/group__CINDEX__TRANSLATION__UNIT.html#gaacd1a1e9d83aaeec6b800e701b3a53f5) and the libcache resource usage is and see if anything seems broken. If that looks alright looking for memory leaks would be the next step.\r\n\r\nI've got 16 GB myself so haven't bothered looking at memory usage at all..."
  },
